cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the problem of 2D hand pose estimation from a monocular RGB image. It also involves the use of graphical models and belief propagation, which are commonly used techniques in computer vision. The paper also proposes a new architecture for this task, which could fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the rotation-invariant aspect of the proposed model could relate to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category, as it could be useful for robotic applications involving hand manipulation. Finally, the evaluation of the proposed model on public datasets could also relate to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
